Subject: RE: [T2] Electric Windshield Washer


I did this on my previous bus a '73. All that was required was to unscrew
the
stock valve from the switch. Fabricate a small bracket in which a "Radio
Shack" micro switch was mounted and screw the bracket back on to the
standard switch. All changes were within the switch housing so it looked
stock.

A neat 'trick' with my set up was to use aquarium air line non return valves
so the jets were always primed and would squirt as soon as the switch was
pressed.

I've posted about this before so it will be in the archives.

good luck
Bob Wallace
Bristol UK
1998 T2
